title: Grateful Dead Live at Deer Creek Music Center on 1990-07-18

description:
Set 1

Help On The Way-> Slipknot!, Franklin's Tower, Minglewood Blues, Easy To Love You, When I Paint My Masterpiece, Brown Eyed Women, Cassidy, Deal

Set 2

China Cat Sunflower-> I Know You Rider, Looks Like Rain, Terrapin Station-> Jam-> Drums-> Jam-> The Other One-> Morning Dew, E: The Weight

reviews.review_text: vintage Neumann recording Outstanding capture.  Its both rich & dynamic with signatures of the pastoral cornfields that surrounded us.  The sound transported me right back to Noblesville.  Middle of nowhere Indiana.

A peach of a show Beautiful tune selection
THE WEIGHT = ENSEMBLE at it's best

Classic summer 1990 Hey folks,   I give this a 4 out of 5 stars !  I thought the 1990 run at Deer Creek was the best of all the times the GD played at the venue.  The weather was perfect, not too hot but hot enough, clear clean farmland air.  All the buzz, was about Deer Creek since it was the smallest venue on the summer tour.  The scene was very laid back in comparison to heavy police presences of later years at the venue.  

Well,  you may say the recording is distant but that was how the PA sound was early in the 1st set.  The crowd was very hip on the 1st Help , Slip , Franklins of the summer tour so we knew this show was going to be a hot one.  The entire 1st set is well played and is very relaxed but still has verve.  Masterpiece, Brown Eyed Women and Peggy-O are stand outs.  A really nice second set with Terrapin Station,  The Other One, and the best Morning Dew I ever saw them play; cap it off with The Weight encore which was relatively new in the set list to a really well played Grateful Dead concert!  

This is my favorite audience source, it's a DAT source with excellent mics and more importantly,  seems to be less on crowd noise.  The 1st set SBD is less to desired; so many folks over look a good audience recording and now with modern remastering some of the audience sources are a marvel.  I wish somebody would take the best aud sources and time align them and have a multiple sources mix down.  I suppose in due time…
